Peter,

I think you&#39;d be better off familiarizing yourself with the details of 
how HyperNEAT works. Novelty Search is a different algorithm altogether, 
for a different class of problems. You probably should familiarize 
yourself with the HyperNEAT algorithm before trying to design an 
experiment. The HyperNEAT user&#39;s page has a lot of really good 
information: http://eplex.cs.ucf.edu/hyperNEATpage/HyperNEAT.html

I&#39;m not familiar with the EPlex&#39;s C++ framework, but SharpNEAT does 
provide a GUI. However, it&#39;s more of an engineer&#39;s GUI, designed to 
visualize your experiment after you set it up in code. I tend to find it 
easier to just use SharpNEAT in a console application. I&#39;ve written some 
tutorials on how to create a SharpNEAT experiment:

http://www.nashcoding.com/2010/07/17/tutorial-evolving-neural-networks-with-sharpneat-2-part-1/

Hope that helps.

Sincerely,
Wesley

